{'contentformat': 'text/x-wiki', 'contentmodel': 'wikitext', '*': '{{PokémonPrevNext/Head|type=Poison|type2=Bug}}\n{{PokémonPrevNext/GO|species=Skorupi}}\n{{PokémonPrevNext/Pokémon|type=Poison|prevnum=450|prev=Hippowdon|nextnum=452|next=Drapion|roundleft=bl|roundright=br}}\n|}\n{{Pokémon Infobox\n|name=Skorupi\n|jname=スコルピ\n|jtranslit=Sukorupi\n|tmname=Scorupi\n|ndex=451\n|sdex=127\n|u2dex=201\n|karea=Mountain\n|kdex=015\n|abrow=173\n|obrow=262\n|opbrow=050\n|typebox=1\n|type1=Poison\n|type2=Bug\n|category=Scorpion\n|height-ftin=2\'07"\n|height-m=0.8\n|weight-lbs=26.5\n|weight-kg=12.0\n|abilityn=d\n|ability1=Battle Armor\n|ability2=Sniper\n|abilityd=Keen Eye\n|egggroupn=2\n|egggroup1=Bug\n|egggroup2=Water 3\n|eggcycles=20\n|evtotal=1\n|evde=1\n|expyield=66\n|oldexp=114\n|lv100exp=1,250,000\n|gendercode=127\n|color=Purple\n|catchrate=120\n|body=14\n|pokefordex=skorupi\n|generation=4\n|friendship=70\n}}\n\'\'\'Skorupi\'\'\' ([[List of Japanese Pokémon names|Japanese]]: \'\'\'スコルピ\'\'\' \'\'Scorupi\'\') is a dual-type {{2t|Poison|Bug}} {{OBP|Pokémon|species}} introduced in [[Generation IV]].\n\nIt [[Evolution|evolve]]s into {{p|Drapion}} starting at [[level]] 40.\n\n==Biology==\nSkorupi resembles an oversized, pale purple scorpion. Its claws and tail have been swapped, giving it two stingers and a claw tail. The miniature jaws, claws, and tail claws are white. Its arms are attached directly to its head, close to its teal eyes. A pointed marking joins its eyes. The head, arms, two tail segments, and all four legs are light blue, while the body, tail end, and other two tail segments are a darker shade of blue.\n\nIt buries itself in sand and lies in wait for unsuspecting prey, gripping it with its tail claws and injecting poison; it will then hold on until the poison takes effect. Skorupi is found in deserts and dry areas like [[Reversal Mountain]], though it can be found in marshy areas such as the [[Great Marsh]].\n\n==In the anime==\n[[File:Team Flare Skorupi.png|thumb|left|250px|Skorupi in the {{pkmn|anime}}]]\n===Major appearances===\nSkorupi debuted in \'\'[[DP099|A Trainer and Child Reunion!]]\'\', under the ownership of {{EF|Aaron}}. It was commonly seen [[Walking Pokémon|outside of its Poké Ball]].\n\nMultiple Skorupi appeared in \'\'[[XY094|From A to Z!]]\'\', \'\'[[XY102|Meeting at Terminus Cave!]]\'\', \'\'[[XY107|An Explosive Operation!]]\'\', and \'\'[[XY132|A Towering Takeover!]]\'\', all under the ownership of {{tc|Team Flare Grunt}}s.\n\n===Minor appearances===\nA {{pkmn|Coordinator}}\'s Skorupi appeared in \'\'[[DP114|Another One Gabites the Dust!]]\'\', where it was seen participating in the [[Appeal|Performance Stage]] of the {{to|Chocovine}} {{pkmn|Contest}}.\n\nA Skorupi appeared in \'\'[[DP125|Battling a Cute Drama!]]\'\', where it was seen at the [[Shelter Town]]\'s [[Pokémon Center]].\n\nA Skorupi appeared in \'\'[[DP140|Historical Mystery Tour!]]\'\'. It was among the Pokémon Ash encountered in [[Xatu\'s Forest]].\n\n==In the manga==\n[[File:Skorupi Adventures.png|thumb|left|115px|Skorupi in [[Pokémon Adventures]]]]\n===In the Pokémon Adventures manga===\nIn \'\'[[PS364|A Skuffle with Skorupi]]\'\', {{adv|Platinum}} tried to catch a Skorupi in the [[Great Marsh]], but she failed and it fled.\n\n[[Team Rocket Elite Trio|Ken]]\'s Skorupi first appeared in \'\'[[PS457|All About Arceus VI]]\'\'.\n\n==In the TCG==\n{{main|Skorupi (TCG)}}\n\n==Game data==\n===NPC appearances===\n{{g|Mystery Dungeon: Explorers of Sky}}: In the Special Episode [[Igglybuff the Prodigy]], Skorupi was a local bully that {{mdc|Wigglytuff|2}}, then an Igglybuff, befriended by giving him and his friend {{p|Banette}} the [[Gummi]]s they demanded, and also going with them to explore the [[Murky Forest]].\n\n===Pokédex entries===\n{{Dex/Header|type=Poison|type2=Bug}}\n{{Dex/NA|gen=IV}}\n{{Dex/Gen/2|gen=IV|reg1=Sinnoh|num1=127|reg2=Johto}}\n{{Dex/Entry1|v=Diamond|entry=It grips prey with its tail claws and injects poison. It tenaciously han